        "title": "Absolute registers are never spelled"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The language has no way to write a raw coordinate. Its one known blind spot: cross-column interleaving finer than the ladder — a row threading between another column's rows."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-r10-body-3": {
      "id": "b-r10-body-3",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "children": [],
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The corpus makes the blind spot measurable: gc's hero row at y=392 threads between pill rows at 96 pitch across a corridor, and the above/below facts flip on 16-48px differences. That interleave is not representable and is the dominant residual loss on "
        },
        {
          "insert": "gc-decomp-harness",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "canvases/gc-decomp-harness.canvas.json"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (90.4% relation against the 93% target). If a future op is added for it, it should be a register offset on "
        },
        {
          "insert": "align",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "30-agent-layout/10-language/70-align",
              "label": "align"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — e.g. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "align y@+128 of config",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — not raw coordinates."
        }
      ]
    }
